@{
    ViewBag.Title = "DailyStory Web Form Examples";
}
<h2>@ViewBag.Title</h2>

<p>To learn more about DailyStory's Web Forms, please visit <a href="https://docs.dailystory.com/acquisition/web-forms/">Web Forms documentation</a> and the <a href="https://docs.dailystory.com/sdk/dotnet#dailystory-web-forms">DailyStory .NET SDK Web Forms APIs</a>.</p>
<p>The examples included use an existing DailyStory application. If you would like to use these samples with your own DailyStory application or <a href="https://login.dailystory.com/trial">trial</a> you will need to update the <code>DailyStory SiteId</code> in web.config and the <code>Web Form Id</code> values in each of the form pages.</p>

<table class="table table-striped">
    <thead>
        <th>Example</th>
        <th>Description</th>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="WebForms/BasicForm_01">Basic Form</a></td>
            <td>Basic web form using the SDK.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="WebForms/BasicForm_02">Basic Form with CSS</a></td>
            <td>Adds DailyStory's base web form style sheet.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="WebForms/BasicForm_03">Basic Form Horiztonal with labels</a></td>
            <td>Uses CSS to show horizontal web form with labels.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="WebForms/BasicForm_04">Basic Form Horiztonal without labels</a></td>
            <td>Uses CSS to show horizontal web form with no labels (<a href="https://docs.dailystory.com/acquisition/web-forms/#form-layout">configured in the Web Form Designer</a>).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="WebForms/CustomForm_01">Advanced CSS Form</a></td>
            <td>Uses custom CSS to display form and Bootstrap for page layout.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="WebForms/CustomForm_02">Custom HTML Form</a></td>
            <td>User defined HTML Form that posts to DailyStory.</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>